<text>
    <body>
        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Introducing John Mathews, the "numeriousness" of whose family takes him to Texas.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>State of Missouri Maddison County</placeName>.</p>

<p><placeName>Fredk Town</placeName> <date when="1825-11-29">Nov 29th 25</date></p>
<p>Dear Sir</p>

<p>The <persName>bearer </persName>of this letter <persName>Mr. Jno Mathews</persName> is an <persName>old and reputable
emegrant to this <placeName>country</placeName> </persName>previous to its cession to the <placeName>United
States</placeName> and has ever since conducted himself in the most upright and <pb n="1237"/>
gentlemanly manner, he owns in this <placeName>neighbourhood</placeName> a large and
valuable, <placeName>farm </placeName>but from the numeriousness of his <persName>family </persName>he in his
old age visits your <placeName>country</placeName> with a view if he likes to become a citizen;
permit me to introduce and recommend him to you as a useful and
valuable citizen and any aid and assistance you can render him whilst
in the <placeName>Spanish provinces</placeName> will confer an Obligation on</p>

<p><persName>M Wilkinson</persName></p>
<p>[Addressed:] <persName>Mr Stephen F. Austin</persName> Province <placeName>Texas</placeName> <persName>Mr Mathews</persName></p>


        </div1>
    </body>
